Your location is used to set the system clock. The first step is to choose the continent where you are located, then you will be able to select your nearest city.
 
UTC - Coordinated Universal Time, abbreviated as UTC, is the primary time standard by which the world regulates clocks and time. It is, within about 1 second, mean solar time at 0Â° longitude; it does not observe daylight saving time. It is one of several closely related successors to Greenwich Mean Time (GMT)
